WEBVTT

00:00.437 --> 00:03.802
Beware! For evil
lurks within these woods!

00:04.426 --> 00:07.872
I, your Pixie guide,
welcome you, brave travelers,

00:07.942 --> 00:09.808
Snotly Goldweaver,

00:09.876 --> 00:11.943
Toshitus Wolfsbane,

00:12.012 --> 00:14.430
Drew of Barrymore.

00:14.465 --> 00:17.349
You must save the fair
maiden from peril.

00:17.367 --> 00:18.500
Oh, no!

00:18.568 --> 00:20.302
Is peril like danger?!

00:20.370 --> 00:21.503
Yes!

00:21.571 --> 00:22.904
We've discussed this.

00:22.973 --> 00:24.572
And it comes in the form

00:24.641 --> 00:27.776
of a red lightning
storm from the warlocks.

00:30.580 --> 00:32.847
A home intruder.

00:32.849 --> 00:36.184
You outrun the storm
on your noble steeds.

00:37.854 --> 00:39.854
And he's on horseback!

00:39.923 --> 00:42.524
I always knew I'd have to kill a horse.

00:42.592 --> 00:46.328
To the west,
you hear a fair goblin maiden.

00:47.397 --> 00:48.596
Help!

00:48.665 --> 00:50.598
I'm imprisoned in an evil warlock's

00:50.667 --> 00:52.334
Tower of Despair!

00:52.402 --> 00:53.868
Save me!

00:53.870 --> 00:56.805
Oh, my God, goblin chicks get me so hot.

00:56.873 --> 00:58.406
What's going on down here?

00:58.474 --> 00:59.941
Oh, hello, traveler!

01:00.010 --> 01:03.478
Welcome to The Dark
Kingdom of Smithurnia!

01:03.547 --> 01:04.879
Pretty awesome, huh?

01:04.881 --> 01:06.748
It's my Dungeons & Dragons masterpiece.

01:06.817 --> 01:10.284
Steve, why do you make it
so hard to love you?

01:10.354 --> 01:11.686
I'll have you know, Mr. Smith,

01:11.755 --> 01:14.622
your son is the best
dungeon master around.

01:14.691 --> 01:18.827
He brings the game to life
by acting out every part!

01:18.895 --> 01:20.628
You flatter me, Snotly!

01:20.697 --> 01:23.698
Dude, she is into you!

01:23.700 --> 01:25.233
Why don't you play with us, dad?

01:25.301 --> 01:26.634
It's a really fun game.

01:26.703 --> 01:28.770
This... This is not a game.

01:28.839 --> 01:30.438
Baseball is a game.

01:30.506 --> 01:32.240
And I'm trying to watch it upstairs.

01:32.308 --> 01:33.775
Baseball's still around?

01:33.844 --> 01:36.378
Is baseball the one
with all the footballs?

01:36.446 --> 01:38.780
Steve, Yoshi, Barney, Slimer,

01:38.849 --> 01:41.783
just keep it quiet down here, okay?

01:43.587 --> 01:46.254
So, how 'bout that goblin maiden?

01:46.322 --> 01:48.790
Is she still... hot to trot?

01:48.859 --> 01:49.924
No.

01:49.993 --> 01:52.460
She's become too crestfallen for love.

01:52.529 --> 01:53.862
Well, does she have a sister?

01:53.930 --> 01:57.732
Yeah, she does, and she's even hotter.

01:57.801 --> 02:00.334
But she has a latex allergy.

02:00.404 --> 02:01.536
Do her anyway!

02:01.605 --> 02:04.005
Pump and pray, bro!

02:06.743 --> 02:09.411
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:09.479 --> 02:13.015
♪ I got a feelin'
that it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

02:13.083 --> 02:16.150
♪ The sun in the sky has
a smile on his face ♪

02:16.152 --> 02:20.422
♪ And he's shinin'
a salute to the American race ♪

02:22.759 --> 02:25.827
♪ Oh, boy, it's swell to say ♪

02:25.896 --> 02:28.296
- ♪ Good... ♪
- ♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:28.364 --> 02:29.498
Aah!

02:30.967 --> 02:33.968
♪ Good morning, U.S.A. ♪

02:36.372 --> 02:37.972
<i>Time for the seventh-inning stretch</i>

02:37.974 --> 02:39.441
<i>with Old Timey Ernie.</i>

02:39.509 --> 02:44.779
♪ <i>Oh! Take me out to the ball game</i> ♪

02:44.848 --> 02:47.515
♪ <i>Take me out with the crowd ♪</i>

02:47.584 --> 02:48.850
- Dad?
- Shh.

02:48.919 --> 02:50.785
I'm observing my favorite
baseball tradition.

02:50.787 --> 02:52.186
"Take Me Out to the Ball Game"

02:52.188 --> 02:54.723
is basically my favorite
song by Albert Von Tilzer,

02:54.791 --> 02:57.191
right behind
"I'm the Lonesomest Gal in Town,"

02:57.193 --> 02:59.728
"Oh, How She Could Yakky
Hacky Wicky Wacky Woo,"

02:59.796 --> 03:01.063
"Honeyboy," "Chili Bean,"

03:01.131 --> 03:02.931
"Put On Your Slippers
and Fill Up Your Pipe,"

03:02.999 --> 03:04.999
"Au Revoir, But Not Goodbye,
Soldier Boy,"

03:05.068 --> 03:06.935
and "My Cutie's Due at Two to Two."

03:07.003 --> 03:11.539
♪ <i>For it's one, two,
three strikes you're out</i> ♪

03:11.608 --> 03:16.144
♪ <i>At the old ball game</i> ♪

03:16.212 --> 03:18.412
Okay. Now you may bother me.

03:19.176 --> 03:20.014
Check it out, Dad.

03:20.083 --> 03:23.017
I made a Dungeons & Dragons
style baseball game!

03:23.086 --> 03:26.554
Your favorite game and my
favorite game combined!

03:26.623 --> 03:28.290
Into...

03:28.358 --> 03:30.424
our favorite game?

03:30.426 --> 03:31.893
- Never.
- Come on, Dad!

03:31.962 --> 03:34.096
Y-Your character is Bill the Shortstop!

03:34.164 --> 03:37.432
He has max ratings in wisdom
and turning double plays.

03:37.501 --> 03:38.633
Just roll the die!

03:38.702 --> 03:41.069
First, I'm going to roll my eyes.

03:44.440 --> 03:47.175
You rolled an 18,
so that's a sacrifice bunt!

03:47.243 --> 03:50.378
- Cool, huh?
- It's the exact opposite of cool.

03:50.447 --> 03:51.445
So...

03:51.447 --> 03:52.580
- hot?
- Damn it!

03:52.649 --> 03:54.182
Why does every temperature mean "good"?

03:54.250 --> 03:56.518
My point is, why make a dumb dice game

03:56.586 --> 03:58.853
when real baseball is happening
right in front of you?

03:58.922 --> 04:01.723
That's an ad for a dating
service for Flat-Earthers.

04:01.792 --> 04:04.326
Yes, but between
the commercials is baseball.

04:04.394 --> 04:05.593
As the world changes,

04:05.662 --> 04:07.862
it's the one thing that stays the same.

04:07.931 --> 04:09.864
It's been uniting fathers and sons

04:09.866 --> 04:11.065
for a hundred years.

04:11.067 --> 04:12.800
But you wouldn't understand, Steve.

04:12.869 --> 04:14.402
You don't even have a son.

04:14.471 --> 04:16.004
<i>And there's Commissioner Mahotz</i>

04:16.072 --> 04:17.872
<i>watching from his luxury box.</i>

04:17.874 --> 04:19.673
<i>He cannot be happy about tonight's</i>

04:19.676 --> 04:20.809
<i>record-low attendance.</i>

04:20.877 --> 04:22.477
<i>Just look at all those fathers</i>

04:22.546 --> 04:26.214
<i>sitting next to empty seats
where their sons should be.</i>

04:26.282 --> 04:27.349
He's right.

04:27.417 --> 04:28.750
It's the sons' fault.

04:28.819 --> 04:30.284
You're someone's son, Steve.

04:30.286 --> 04:32.086
Maybe you can tell me why
our Little League field

04:32.156 --> 04:33.421
was turned into a dog park.

04:33.490 --> 04:34.689
That was actually a measure

04:34.758 --> 04:35.957
presented to the voters last...

04:36.026 --> 04:39.161
And I voted yes!
The dogs need a place to go!

04:41.165 --> 04:42.764
- Git! Git!
- What's happening?

04:42.833 --> 04:44.833
One minute till "Sex Hospital" starts!

04:44.901 --> 04:46.234
Quick! Set everything up!

04:46.302 --> 04:47.969
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God! Hurry!

